net.proteusframework.processes.form.cms

Class FormEntryComponentApplication

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.MIWTApplication
      • net.proteusframework.processes.form.cms.FormEntryComponentApplication
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable, EventListener, net.proteusframework.core.locale.LocaleContextSource, net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.event.NotificationListener

    public class FormEntryComponentApplication
extends net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.MIWTApplication
    MIWTApplication for displaying a FormEntryComponent. Old way was to use a SiteAwareMIWTApplication, but there wasn't a good way to configure the FormEntryComponent, e.g. from a FormEntryBeanGenerator. Eventually we should have better integration between MIWT and CMS, then this application could be replaced. For now, this application just creates a FormEntryComponent and has a property to set the FormControllerConfig. If the config is not set, nothing will be displayed. When the config is set, it clears the UI and initializes the form.
    Author:
    jcrosmer@i2rd.com
